node.text:
Today, we're making a creamy & delicious smoothie with @talenti 🥭Alphonso Mango Sorbetto and durian! #TalentiPartner

Durian and Mango are some of my favorite tropical fruits. I also had a lot of fun cracking open that durian!

👉Recipe:
1 cup of Durian (deseeded)
1 cup of Plan-based Milk
1 Tablespoon of Chia Seeds
1/2 of a banana
3 Scoops of @talenti Alphonso Mango Sorbetto
1/2 cup of ice
1 Extra Scoop of @talenti Alphonso Mango Sorbetto (as a garnish to be added after blending)

@talenti Sorbetto is available at @costco warehouses in the Bay Area as a 4-pack! These (3) flavors are the most popular: 🥭Alphonso Mango Sorbetto, Roman Raspberry Sorbetto, 🍓Strawberry Hibiscus Sorbetto. The Sorbettos are Dairy Free, Gluten-Free, and suitable for a Vegan Diet🌱. Make sure to take advantage of the offer to save on Talenti Sorbetto from Costco this summer!
👉Find out more info by visiting the link in my bio !

I had an amazing time checking out the ‘Taste of Orleans’ event at @cagreatamerica !🎢

(Flight Deck and Celebration Swings are my current favorite rides!)
It was really fun tasting all the different dishes they had.

👉Make sure to check out their 'Taste of Orleans' event which is available from July 17 - August 1.

🎉Click the link in my bio to purchase your tickets to @cagreatamerica today!
#sponsored #CAGreatAmerica

node.text:
🥓Making a simple Crispy Pork Belly Sisig today!🍚
One of my favorite Filipino dishes. Let me know how you guys like these recipe vids!
-
1lb pork belly
Braise for 30 mins in 1 cup soy sauce, 2 tablespoon vinegar, and enough water to cover the pork belly.
Dry pork belly over night.
Make holes in the pork belly skin with a fork (or something sharp) before deep frying.
Deep fry for 5 to 8 minutes at 350f or until skin blisters.
Take out pork belly and chop it up.
-
Chop up a small onion, 2 cloves of garlic, and 1 jalapeno. Get juice of a whole lemon.
Caramelize onion and garlic on pan then add jalapeno (i also added 2 thai chilis for extra spicy). Afterwards, add porkbelly and add salt/soy sauce until desired taste. Add lemon juice and then serve!
